{{Infobox sport tournament | name = 1958 Basque Pelota World Championships | image = 1958 Basque Pelota World Championships poster.png | caption = Tournament poster | location = {{flagicon|France}} [[Biarritz]], [[France]] | start_date = 11 | end_date = 21 September | administrator = [[International Federation of Basque Pelota|FIPV]] | tournament_format = | venues = | teams = 9+ | purse = | champions = {{flag|France}} | runners-up1 = {{flag|Spain}} | runners-up2 = {{flag|Argentina}} | matches = | points = | attendance = | previous = [[1955 Basque Pelota World Championships|1955]] | next = [[1962 Basque Pelota World Championships|1962]] | website = }}
The '''1958 Basque Pelota World Championships''' were the 3rd edition of the [[Basque Pelota World Championships]] organized by the [[International Federation of Basque Pelota|FIPV]].
==Participating nations== {{col-begin|width=70%}} {{col-break}} *{{flag|Argentina}} *{{flag|Cuba}} *{{flag|France}} *{{flag|Italy}} {{col-break}} *{{flag|Mexico}} *{{flag|Philippines}} *{{flag|Spain}} *{{flag|United States}} {{col-break}} *{{flag|Uruguay}} *Others {{col-end}}
==Events== A total of 17 events were disputed, in 5 playing areas.<ref>{{cite web| author=Javier Solano| title=Historia de los Mundiales| date=November 2004| language=Spanish| url=http://fipv.net/images/historial/MUNDIALES_1952-1998.pdf#page=10| accessdate=20 September 2016}}</ref>
