{{infobox country at games | NPC = MEX | NPCname = [http://www.deporte.org.mx/ Federacion Mexicana de Deporte] | games = Winter Paralympics | year = 2006 | flagcaption = | oldcode = | website = | location = [[Turin]] | competitors = 1 | sports = 1 | flagbearer = | rank = | gold = 0 | silver = 0 | bronze = 0 | officials = | appearances = auto | app_begin_year = 2006 | app_end_year = | summerappearances = | winterappearances = | seealso = }}
'''[[Mexico]]''' participated in the ninth '''[[2006 Winter Paralympics|Winter Paralympics]]''' in [[Turin]], [[Italy]], entering one athlete. [[Mexico]] was the only nation participating in the [[Paralympics]] that did not send a delegation to the [[2006 Winter Olympics|Torino Olympics]].
[[Paralympic alpine skiing|Alpine skier]] [[Armando Ruiz]] (LW 11, b. August 27, 1963), a lawyer from [[Mexico City]], competed in the [[giant slalom]], finishing 41st out of 41 finishers in the men's sitting category with a combined two-run adjusted time of 5:43.45, nearly four minutes behind winner [[Martin Braxenthaler]] of [[Germany at the 2006 Winter Paralympics|Germany]] and nearly three minutes behind 40th-place finisher [[Xavier Barios]] of [[Andorra at the 2006 Winter Paralympics|Andorra]]. It was the first ski race he had ever competed in, and he received a huge ovation from the crowd after completing each run.
Ruiz was one of the 3 men finalists for the Whang Youn Dai Overcome Prize of the Paralympic Games.
